title: S.J. boys: Williamstown downs Bordentown in Coaches Tournament
text:
Rancocas Valley 6, Delsea 1: Danny Morgan had two goals for the third-seeded home team against the 14th-seed. Luis Rivadeneira had three assists.
OLYMPIC CONFERENCE 
Cherry Hill East 1, Cherry Hill West 0: Zach Fox scored the visitors lone goal on a throw in from Olin McClendon to give coach Mike Melograna his first win over Cherry Hill West. Lee Rosen-Swell had seven saves. 
Camden Catholic 3, Bishop Eustace 2: Jay Lee had two goals on the road for the Irish. Alessandro Arcioni also scored. 
NONLEAGUE 
Hammonton 2, Penns Grove 1, OT: Tyler Oster and Vincent Piccari each scored for the hosts. Devin Piro made four saves. 
GCIT 2, Cumberland 1: John Beck had two goals to power the home team. Joe Milano had eight saves. 
Schalick 3, Triton 1: Michael D'Orio scored two goals for the visitors. Tyler Lunsford also scored. 
CAPE-ATLANTIC LEAGUE 
Oakcrest 2, Millville 1: Ryan Elkner and Tom Vieyra each had a goal at home. Jack Markley stopped six shots. 
TRI-COUNTY CLASSIC 
Pennsville 4, Clayton 1: Josh White scored two goals on the road. Tyler Russykevicz and Austin Morgan also scored. Daemon Durham made six saves. 
Wildwood 5, Salem 1: Will Helm and Dennis McAllister each scored two goals for the hosts. Brendan Bean made eight saves. 
BURLINGTON COUNTY LEAGUE 
Palmyra 3, Pemberton 1: Jon Unterkoeffler, Ryan Carducci and Damien Jennings each had a goal on the road. Jennings also had an assist. 
Maple Shade 7, Westampton Tech 1: Devin Plumlee had a hat trick to help his team at home. Doran Keys and Brandon Henry each had two assists. 
COLONIAL CONFERENCE 
Gateway 9, Overbrook 0: Nick Steigerwald and Tyler Kizitaff each scored two goals to lead the visitors. Jack Eckstein and Micsha LeGoff each had two assists.
